events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — Scoot Henderson had 22 points and 10 assists and the Portland Trail Blazers beat Brandon Miller and the Charlotte Hornets 89-86 on Wednesday night in a matchup of two of the league’s top three draft picks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Scoot Henderson outduels Brandon Miller as Trail Blazers beat Hornets 89-86 to snap 10-game skid

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis scored 19 of his 35 points in the first quarter and had 18 rebounds, helping the Los Angeles Lakers beat the Washington Wizards 125-120 on Wednesday night for their eighth victory in nine games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis leads Lakers to their 8th win in 9 games, scores 35 points in 125-120 victory over Wizards

headlines.description: — Jalen Johnson had 28 points, 14 rebounds and 11 assists for his first career triple-double and the Atlanta Hawks overcame a 50-point effort by Detroit's Malachi Flynn for a 121-113 win over the Pistons on Wednesday night that clinched a berth in the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Johnson has 28 points, 14 rebounds, Hawks clinch play-in berth with 121-113 win over Pistons

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Oklahoma City coach Mark Daigneault likened the Celtics' performance this season to that of a Ferrari.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis scores 27, Celtics earn home-court advantage in playoffs with 135-100 win over Thunder

headlines.description: — Cam Thomas scored 27 points, rookie Noah Clowney had a career-high 22 points and 10 rebounds, and the Brooklyn Nets outlasted the Indiana Pacers 115-111 on Wednesday night to split a home-and-home set.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets outlast Pacers 115-111, still eliminated from postseason contention

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. scored 35 points to lead the Memphis Grizzlies to an 111-101 victory over the Milwaukee Bucks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaren Jackson Jr. scores 35 points in Grizzlies' 111-101 win over Bucks

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 28 points, Naz Reid added 23 and the Minnesota Timberwolves routed the short-handed Toronto Raptors 133-85 on Wednesday night to move into a tie for first-place in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards, Reid help Timberwolves rout Raptors 133-85 to move into tie for first in West

events.name: Orlando Magic at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — The physical, swarming play of Paolo Banchero and the Orlando Magic so frustrated New Orleans that three Pelicans players were ejected in the game's final seconds.
headlines.shortLinkText: Banchero's 32 points lifts Magic over Pelicans, Zion Williamson injures his finger

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 40 points, Kevin Durant added 32 and the Phoenix Suns beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 122-101 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 40, Durant adds 32, Suns improve playoff position with a 122-101 win over Cavs
